<main id="content" class="content"> <header> <h1 class="title">Christmas Prayer</h1>
 <p class="subtitle" role="doc-subtitle">Dec 25, 2016 00:00</p>
</header> <p>
Who am I this Christmas Day?
</p>

 <p>
Am I an angel, bringing good news to those who yearn to hear it?
</p>

 <p>
Am I a shepherd, who runs to see what God has done?
</p>

 <p>
Am I a Magi, willing to give any gift to the King?
</p>

 <p>
Am I Joseph, listening to any way that God might speak? <br></br></p>

 <p>
Am I Mary, saying yes when others would jeer?
</p>

 <p>
In the moments of stillness, <br></br>
when all pretensions are dropped, <br></br>
I fear that I may be Herod, <br></br>
safe and comfortable, <br></br>
but afraid of what might change. <br></br></p>

 <p>
Lord, you know my true self, <br></br>
both what I am <br></br>
and what I can be, <br></br>
by your grace. <br></br></p>

 <p>
 <i>Amen</i>
</p>


